<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I’ve been learning Emacs primarily for Org and Org-roam, and I’m enjoying it all immensely. Today, I customized an Ubersicht widget on my MacBook to open Emacs maximized (a pain in the Mac),and to open with various command line functions (run a “morning” keyboard macro that sets up buffers for my morning routine, open a new journal entry, and open my main agenda view). </p> <p>Emacs is taking over!</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/columbcille"> /u/columbcille </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://i.redd.it/xiycqd8xtcg91.jpg">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/wipscv/emacs_newbie_but_proud_of_myself/">[comments]</a></span>